{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"There's a man out there, somewhere,"},{"time":2880,"text":"who looks a little bit\nlike the actor Idris Elba,"},{"time":5880,"text":"or at least he did 20 years ago."},{"time":8280,"text":"I don't know anything else about him,"},{"time":10120,"text":"except that he once saved my life"},{"time":12040,"text":"by putting his own life in danger."},{"time":14600,"text":"This man ran across four lanes of freeway\ntraffic in the middle of the night"},{"time":20000,"text":"to bring me back to safety"},{"time":21800,"text":"after a car accident\nthat could have killed me."},{"time":24600,"text":"And the whole thing\nleft me really shaken up, obviously,"},{"time":27280,"text":"but it also left me with this\nkind of burning, gnawing need"},{"time":31280,"text":"to understand why he did it,"},{"time":33760,"text":"what forces within him\ncaused him to make the choice"},{"time":36560,"text":"that I owe my life to,"},{"time":38440,"text":"to risk his own life\nto save the life of a stranger?"},{"time":42080,"text":"In other words, what are the causes of his\nor anybody else's capacity for altruism?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":47840,"text":"But first let me tell you what happened."},{"time":49880,"text":"That night, I was 19 years old"},{"time":51360,"text":"and driving back to my home\nin Tacoma, Washington,"},{"time":53760,"text":"down the Interstate 5 freeway,"},{"time":55600,"text":"when a little dog\ndarted out in front of my car."},{"time":58160,"text":"And I did exactly\nwhat you're not supposed to do,"},{"time":60520,"text":"which is swerve to avoid it."},{"time":62480,"text":"And I discovered why\nyou're not supposed to do that."},{"time":65319,"text":"I hit the dog anyways,"},{"time":67080,"text":"and that sent the car into a fishtail,"},{"time":69720,"text":"and then a spin across the freeway,"},{"time":72320,"text":"until finally it wound up\nin the fast lane of the freeway"},{"time":75920,"text":"faced backwards into oncoming traffic"},{"time":78880,"text":"and then the engine died."},{"time":81480,"text":"And I was sure in that moment\nthat I was about to die too,"},{"time":85880,"text":"but I didn't"},{"time":87120,"text":"because of the actions\nof that one brave man"},{"time":89880,"text":"who must have made the decision"},{"time":91400,"text":"within a fraction of a second\nof seeing my stranded car"},{"time":94440,"text":"to pull over and run\nacross four lanes of freeway traffic"},{"time":98720,"text":"in the dark"},{"time":100680,"text":"to save my life."},{"time":102680,"text":"And then after he got my car working again"},{"time":105600,"text":"and got me back to safety\nand made sure I was going to be all right,"},{"time":109240,"text":"he drove off again."},{"time":110800,"text":"He never even told me his name,"},{"time":113160,"text":"and I'm pretty sure\nI forgot to say thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116440,"text":"So before I go any further,"},{"time":118400,"text":"I really want to take a moment"},{"time":119880,"text":"to stop and say thank you\nto that stranger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123280,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":130919,"text":"I tell you all of this"},{"time":132160,"text":"because the events of that night changed\nthe course of my life to some degree."},{"time":136400,"text":"I became a psychology researcher,"},{"time":138040,"text":"and I've devoted my work to understanding\nthe human capacity to care for others."},{"time":142840,"text":"Where does it come from,\nand how does it develop,"},{"time":145200,"text":"and what are the extreme forms\nthat it can take?"},{"time":148120,"text":"These questions are really important\nto understanding basic aspects"},{"time":151320,"text":"of human social nature."},{"time":153320,"text":"A lot of people,\nand this includes everybody"},{"time":155440,"text":"from philosophers\nand economists to ordinary people"},{"time":158360,"text":"believe that human nature\nis fundamentally selfish,"},{"time":161640,"text":"that we're only ever really motivated\nby our own welfare."},{"time":165840,"text":"But if that's true, why do some people,\nlike the stranger who rescued me,"},{"time":170160,"text":"do selfless things,\nlike helping other people"},{"time":172680,"text":"at enormous risk and cost to themselves?"},{"time":175880,"text":"Answering this question"},{"time":177200,"text":"requires exploring the roots\nof extraordinary acts of altruism,"},{"time":181320,"text":"and what might make people\nwho engage in such acts"},{"time":183720,"text":"different than other people."},{"time":185600,"text":"But until recently, very little work\non this topic had been done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189920,"text":"The actions of the man who rescued me"},{"time":191760,"text":"meet the most stringent\ndefinition of altruism,"},{"time":194760,"text":"which is a voluntary, costly behavior"},{"time":197400,"text":"motivated by the desire\nto help another individual."},{"time":200640,"text":"So it's a selfless act\nintended to benefit only the other."},{"time":204560,"text":"What could possibly\nexplain an action like that?"},{"time":208120,"text":"One answer is compassion, obviously,"},{"time":210080,"text":"which is a key driver of altruism."},{"time":212520,"text":"But then the question becomes,"},{"time":214160,"text":"why do some people\nseem to have more of it than others?"},{"time":218120,"text":"And the answer may be that the brains\nof highly altruistic people"},{"time":222040,"text":"are different in fundamental ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225120,"text":"But to figure out how,"},{"time":227040,"text":"I actually started from the opposite end,"},{"time":230160,"text":"with psychopaths."},{"time":232680,"text":"A common approach to understanding\nbasic aspects of human nature,"},{"time":235800,"text":"like the desire to help other people,"},{"time":237840,"text":"is to study people\nin whom that desire is missing,"},{"time":241000,"text":"and psychopaths are exactly such a group."},{"time":244200,"text":"Psychopathy is a developmental disorder"},{"time":246600,"text":"with strongly genetic origins,"},{"time":248720,"text":"and it results in a personality\nthat's cold and uncaring"},{"time":251640,"text":"and a tendency to engage in antisocial\nand sometimes very violent behavior."},{"time":256040,"text":"Once my colleagues and I\nat the National Institute of Mental Health"},{"time":259320,"text":"conducted some of the first ever\nbrain imaging research"},{"time":261959,"text":"of psychopathic adolescents,"},{"time":264120,"text":"and our findings, and the findings\nof other researchers now,"},{"time":267000,"text":"have shown that people\nwho are psychopathic"},{"time":269320,"text":"pretty reliably exhibit\nthree characteristics."},{"time":273160,"text":"First, although they're not generally\ninsensitive to other people's emotions,"},{"time":277800,"text":"they are insensitive to signs\nthat other people are in distress."},{"time":281600,"text":"And in particular,"},{"time":282840,"text":"they have difficulty recognizing\nfearful facial expressions like this one."},{"time":286760,"text":"And fearful expressions convey\nurgent need and emotional distress,"},{"time":290480,"text":"and they usually elicit\ncompassion and a desire to help"},{"time":293120,"text":"in people who see them,"},{"time":294400,"text":"so it makes sense that people\nwho tend to lack compassion"},{"time":297120,"text":"also tend to be insensitive to these cues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300520,"text":"The part of the brain"},{"time":301760,"text":"that's the most important\nfor recognizing fearful expressions"},{"time":304680,"text":"is called the amygdala."},{"time":305960,"text":"There are very rare cases of people\nwho lack amygdalas completely,"},{"time":309400,"text":"and they're profoundly impaired\nin recognizing fearful expressions."},{"time":313280,"text":"And whereas healthy adults and children"},{"time":315680,"text":"usually show big spikes\nin amygdala activity"},{"time":318320,"text":"when they look at fearful expressions,"},{"time":320480,"text":"psychopaths' amygdalas\nare underreactive to these expressions."},{"time":323640,"text":"Sometimes they don't react at all,"},{"time":325320,"text":"which may be why they have\ntrouble detecting these cues."},{"time":329240,"text":"Finally, psychopaths' amygdalas\nare smaller than average"},{"time":332400,"text":"by about 18 or 20 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334920,"text":"So all of these findings\nare reliable and robust,"},{"time":338760,"text":"and they're very interesting."},{"time":340240,"text":"But remember that my main interest"},{"time":341920,"text":"is not understanding\nwhy people don't care about others."},{"time":345480,"text":"It's understanding why they do."},{"time":347880,"text":"So the real question is,"},{"time":350200,"text":"could extraordinary altruism,"},{"time":352480,"text":"which is the opposite of psychopathy"},{"time":354720,"text":"in terms of compassion\nand the desire to help other people,"},{"time":358160,"text":"emerge from a brain that is also\nthe opposite of psychopathy?"},{"time":362200,"text":"A sort of antipsychopathic brain,"},{"time":365880,"text":"better able to recognize\nother people's fear,"},{"time":369000,"text":"an amygdala that's more reactive\nto this expression"},{"time":371440,"text":"and maybe larger than average as well?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":373920,"text":"As my research has now shown,"},{"time":375960,"text":"all three things are true."},{"time":377440,"text":"And we discovered this"},{"time":378720,"text":"by testing a population\nof truly extraordinary altruists."},{"time":381760,"text":"These are people who have given\none of their own kidneys"},{"time":384440,"text":"to a complete stranger."},{"time":386600,"text":"So these are people who have volunteered\nto undergo major surgery"},{"time":389720,"text":"so that one of their own\nhealthy kidneys can be removed"},{"time":392360,"text":"and transplanted into a very ill stranger"},{"time":394440,"text":"that they've never met and may never meet."},{"time":397040,"text":"\"Why would anybody do this?\"\nis a very common question."},{"time":400520,"text":"And the answer may be"},{"time":401920,"text":"that the brains of these\nextraordinary altruists"},{"time":404200,"text":"have certain special characteristics."},{"time":407040,"text":"They are better at recognizing\nother people's fear."},{"time":410280,"text":"They're literally better at detecting\nwhen somebody else is in distress."},{"time":413720,"text":"This may be in part because their amygdala\nis more reactive to these expressions."},{"time":418400,"text":"And remember, this is the same part\nof the brain that we found"},{"time":421360,"text":"was underreactive\nin people who are psychopathic."},{"time":423720,"text":"And finally, their amygdalas\nare larger than average as well,"},{"time":426640,"text":"by about eight percent."},{"time":427880,"text":"So together, what these data suggest"},{"time":429640,"text":"is the existence of something\nlike a caring continuum in the world"},{"time":433280,"text":"that's anchored at the one end\nby people who are highly psychopathic,"},{"time":436840,"text":"and at the other by people\nwho are very compassionate"},{"time":439360,"text":"and driven to acts of extreme altruism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442760,"text":"But I should add that what makes\nextraordinary altruists so different"},{"time":446720,"text":"is not just that they're\nmore compassionate than average."},{"time":449440,"text":"They are,"},{"time":450680,"text":"but what's even more unusual about them"},{"time":452600,"text":"is that they're compassionate\nand altruistic"},{"time":454720,"text":"not just towards people\nwho are in their own innermost circle"},{"time":457680,"text":"of friends and family. Right?"},{"time":459680,"text":"Because to have compassion for people\nthat you love and identify with"},{"time":462960,"text":"is not extraordinary."},{"time":466040,"text":"Truly extraordinary altruists' compassion\nextends way beyond that circle,"},{"time":470240,"text":"even beyond their wider\ncircle of acquaintances"},{"time":472480,"text":"to people who are outside\ntheir social circle altogether,"},{"time":475440,"text":"total strangers,"},{"time":477000,"text":"just like the man who rescued me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479960,"text":"And I've had the opportunity now\nto ask a lot of altruistic kidney donors"},{"time":483480,"text":"how it is that they manage to generate\nsuch a wide circle of compassion"},{"time":487880,"text":"that they were willing to give\na complete stranger their kidney."},{"time":491240,"text":"And I found it's a really difficult\nquestion for them to answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494760,"text":"I say, \"How is it that\nyou're willing to do this thing"},{"time":498840,"text":"when so many other people don't?"},{"time":500840,"text":"You're one of fewer than 2,000 Americans"},{"time":503280,"text":"who has ever given a kidney to a stranger."},{"time":505920,"text":"What is it that makes you so special?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":508400,"text":"And what do they say?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":511400,"text":"They say, \"Nothing."},{"time":514200,"text":"There's nothing special about me."},{"time":516000,"text":"I'm just the same as everybody else.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":519200,"text":"And I think that's actually\na really telling answer,"},{"time":522320,"text":"because it suggests that the circles\nof these altruists don't look like this,"},{"time":527240,"text":"they look more like this."},{"time":529240,"text":"They have no center."},{"time":531320,"text":"These altruists literally\ndon't think of themselves"},{"time":533760,"text":"as being at the center of anything,"},{"time":536040,"text":"as being better or more inherently\nimportant than anybody else."},{"time":540000,"text":"When I asked one altruist\nwhy donating her kidney made sense to her,"},{"time":543240,"text":"she said, \"Because it's not about me.\""},{"time":547040,"text":"Another said,"},{"time":548800,"text":"\"I'm not different. I'm not unique."},{"time":551080,"text":"Your study here is going to find out\nthat I'm just the same as you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":554440,"text":"I think the best description\nfor this amazing lack of self-centeredness"},{"time":558560,"text":"is humility,"},{"time":560440,"text":"which is that quality\nthat in the words of St. Augustine"},{"time":563560,"text":"makes men as angels."},{"time":566120,"text":"And why is that?"},{"time":567840,"text":"It's because if there's\nno center of your circle,"},{"time":570640,"text":"there can be no inner rings\nor outer rings,"},{"time":573200,"text":"nobody who is more or less worthy\nof your care and compassion"},{"time":576120,"text":"than anybody else."},{"time":577920,"text":"And I think that this is what really\ndistinguishes extraordinary altruists"},{"time":581440,"text":"from the average person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583400,"text":"But I also think that this is a view\nof the world that's attainable by many"},{"time":587000,"text":"and maybe even most people."},{"time":589000,"text":"And I think this\nbecause at the societal level,"},{"time":591280,"text":"expansions of altruism and compassion\nare already happening everywhere."},{"time":595920,"text":"The psychologist Steven Pinker\nand others have shown"},{"time":598400,"text":"that all around the world people\nare becoming less and less accepting"},{"time":601680,"text":"of suffering in ever-widening\ncircles of others,"},{"time":604160,"text":"which has led to declines\nof all kinds of cruelty and violence,"},{"time":607240,"text":"from animal abuse to domestic violence\nto capital punishment."},{"time":611480,"text":"And it's led to increases\nin all kinds of altruism."},{"time":614320,"text":"A hundred years ago, people\nwould have thought it was ludicrous"},{"time":617440,"text":"how normal and ordinary it is"},{"time":618960,"text":"for people to donate\ntheir blood and bone marrow"},{"time":622280,"text":"to complete strangers today."},{"time":624720,"text":"Is it possible that\na hundred years from now"},{"time":626840,"text":"people will think\nthat donating a kidney to a stranger"},{"time":629440,"text":"is just as normal and ordinary"},{"time":630920,"text":"as we think donating blood\nand bone marrow is today?"},{"time":633960,"text":"Maybe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635800,"text":"So what's at the root\nof all these amazing changes?"},{"time":638720,"text":"In part it seems to be"},{"time":640520,"text":"increases in wealth\nand standards of living."},{"time":644600,"text":"As societies become\nwealthier and better off,"},{"time":647360,"text":"people seem to turn\ntheir focus of attention outward,"},{"time":650000,"text":"and as a result, all kinds of altruism\ntowards strangers increases,"},{"time":653880,"text":"from volunteering to charitable donations\nand even altruistic kidney donations."},{"time":659440,"text":"But all of these changes also yield"},{"time":662440,"text":"a strange and paradoxical result,"},{"time":665680,"text":"which is that even as the world is\nbecoming a better and more humane place,"},{"time":669240,"text":"which it is,"},{"time":670480,"text":"there's a very common perception\nthat it's becoming worse"},{"time":673200,"text":"and more cruel, which it's not."},{"time":676080,"text":"And I don't know exactly why this is,"},{"time":677920,"text":"but I think it may be\nthat we now just know so much more"},{"time":681520,"text":"about the suffering\nof strangers in distant places,"},{"time":684720,"text":"and so we now care a lot more"},{"time":687160,"text":"about the suffering\nof those distant strangers."},{"time":690240,"text":"But what's clear is the kinds\nof changes we're seeing show"},{"time":693960,"text":"that the roots of altruism and compassion"},{"time":696440,"text":"are just as much a part of human nature\nas cruelty and violence,"},{"time":699480,"text":"maybe even more so,"},{"time":701200,"text":"and while some people do seem\nto be inherently more sensitive"},{"time":705280,"text":"to the suffering of distant others,"},{"time":707400,"text":"I really believe that the ability\nto remove oneself"},{"time":710200,"text":"from the center of the circle"},{"time":712000,"text":"and expand the circle of compassion\noutward to include even strangers"},{"time":716080,"text":"is within reach for almost everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720080,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721320,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}